FBIS4-64413 "drweu085_q_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-085 Daily Report 2 May 1994 TURKEY Government on Reopening Border Gate With Iraq Government on Reopening Border Gate With Iraq TA0205160094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 2 May 94 TA0205160094 Ankara ANATOLIA English BFN [Text] Diyarbakir, May 2 (A.A.) -- Deputy Prime Minister Murat Karayalcin said on Monday [2 May] that the government would evaluate reopening the Habur border gate which borders Turkey and Iraq. Karayalcin speaking to reporters at his arrival in southeastern Diyarbakir Province for studies on the Habur border gate which is near the township of Silopi in the province of Sirnak said reopening this border gate was very important for trade in the southeast.
